Third Department,

September, 1941.

(September 15, 1941.) The People of the State of New York ex rel. George Bennett, Appellant, v. Walter B. Martin, as Warden of Clinton Prison, Dannemora, N. Y., Respondent.

Leave to appeal on typewritten record has already been granted. Application to extend time within which to perfect appeal granted and time extended for six months. Present — Hill, P. J., Bliss, Heffernan, Sehenck and Foster, JJ.
